---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';

const updated = 'June 2026';
---

<Layout title="Privacy" description="How Allocate handles your data: on-device storage, iCloud sync, no account, no backend.">
  <section class="section prose-section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        {SITE.name} is built so that your financial data stays yours. This page
        explains, in plain language, what the app does and does not do with your
        information.
      </p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Your transactions are stored on your Mac and synced through your own iCloud.</li>
        <li>There is no {SITE.name} account and no custom backend server that holds your data.</li>
        <li>We do not sell, share, or monetize your financial information.</li>
        <li>You can export everything to CSV and delete it at any time.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What data the app stores</h2>
      <p>
        When you import a bank statement, {SITE.name} extracts transactions —
        dates, descriptions, amounts, and categories — and stores them locally
        on your device using Apple's SwiftData. If you enable iCloud, this data
        syncs to your personal iCloud account so it is available across your
        devices. It is never sent to servers operated by {SITE.name}.
      </p>

      <h2>AI categorization</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} uses an AI agent to categorize transactions, and it runs on
        your Mac. By default extraction happens locally on your device; if you
        prefer, you can connect your own ChatGPT account instead. Either way, your
        statements are not sent to servers operated by {SITE.name}, and the data
        is only used to categorize the statement you imported — never to identify
        you or build a profile.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics on this website</h2>
      <p>
        This website may use a privacy-friendly, cookieless analytics service
        (Cloudflare Web Analytics) to count aggregate page views and downloads.
        It does not use cookies, does not track you across sites, and does not
        collect personally identifiable information. It tells us how many people
        visit — never who they are.
      </p>

      <h2>Identification &amp; rate limiting</h2>
      <p>
        A future release may use anonymous device authentication purely to
        rate-limit automated abuse of the AI service. This identifies a device,
        not a person, and is not linked to your financial data.
      </p>

      <h2>Your control</h2>
      <p>
        Because your data lives on your own device and iCloud, you are always in
        control. Export it to CSV whenever you like, or delete it from the app
        and from iCloud to remove it entirely.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Contact details will be published here
        alongside the app's release.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }
  .prose ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .prose p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
